<h2>Server</h2>

<p>
	This page shows server states and provides administrative tasks.<br>
	<br>
</p>

<h4>Status</h4>

<table class="table table-bordered">

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Version:</b></td>
		<td><%= cluster.attr('version') %> (built by <%=
			cluster.attr('built_by') %> on <%= cluster.attr('built_time') %>)</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Mode:</b></td>
		<td><% if (cluster.attr('maintenance')) { %> <span
			class="label label-important">Maintenance Mode</span> <% } else { %>
			<span class="label label-success">Running</span> <% } %>
		</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Queue:</b></td>
		<td><% if (cluster.attr('blocked')) { %> <span
			class="label label-important">Blocked</span> <% } else { %> <span
			class="label label-success">Running</span> <% } %>

		</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Threads Queue:</b></td>
		<td><%= cluster.attr('threads') %></td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Max Jobs:</b></td>
		<td><%= cluster.attr('max_jobs') %></td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Max Jobs per User:</b></td>
		<td><%= cluster.attr('max_jobs_user') %></td>
	</tr>

</table>

<hr>

<h4>Server</h4>

<table class="table table-bordered">

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Disk Usage:</b></td>
		<td>	
		<div class="progress progress-info" style="width: 150px;">
		  <div class="bar" style="width: <%== ((cluster.attr('total_disc_space') - cluster.attr('free_disc_space')) / cluster.attr('total_disc_space') * 100) %>%"></div>
		</div><%== cluster.attr('total_disc_space') - cluster.attr('free_disc_space') %> GB used, <b><%== cluster.attr('free_disc_space') %> GB free</b>
		</td> 		
	
	</tr>

</table>

<hr>

<h4>Hadoop</h4>

<table class="table table-bordered">

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Mode:</b></td>
		<td><% if (cluster.attr('safemode')) { %> <span
			class="label label-important">SAFEMODE!</span> <% } else { %> <span
			class="label label-success">Running</span> <% } %>
		</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td style="width: 150px;"><b>Details:</b></td>
		<td><pre><%== cluster.attr('cluster') %></pre></td>
	</tr>
</table>

<hr>


<h4>Maintenance Mode</h4>
<p>Maintenance mode is for preventing any users other than
	administrators from submitting jobs. The front page will appear as
	normal when your site is in maintenance mode. Users will only see the
	maintenance mode message when they attempt to submit a job.</p>
<p>
	<i>Note: You can create a customized maintenance mode message by
		change the MAINTENANCE_MESSAGE variable (see Settings).</i>
</p>
<br>
<p>
	<a href="/admin/maintenance/enter" class="btn btn-danger">Enter
		Maintenance Mode</a> <a href="/admin/maintenance/exit"
		class="btn btn-success">Exit Maintenance Mode</a>
</p>


<hr>


<h4>Queue</h4>
<p>Blocks the queue. All running jobs are executed and all other
	jobs are waiting until the queue is manually opened.</p>
<br>
<p>
	<a href="/admin/queue/block" class="btn btn-danger">Block Queue</a> <a
		href="/admin/queue/open" class="btn btn-success">Open Queue</a>
</p>

<hr>


<h4>Auto Retire</h4>
<p>Retires old jobs and send notifications.</p>
<br>
<p>
	<a href="/api/v2/admin/jobs/retire" class="btn btn-primary">Start Retire</a>
</p>
